  "riddle": "1. Track down the page that outlines the governing body of a southern Indian state, and reveal how many representatives serve within its hallowed halls.\n\n2. What is the height at which this seat of power stands above sea level? Make haste to uncover the elevation of its physical structure.\n\n3. Cast your eyes around this assembly; how many houses of worship can you find nearby? Seek out the count of churches in the vicinity.\n\n4. If you were to combine the elevation you just uncovered in clue 2 with the number of nearby churches from clue 3, what sum would grace your findings? \n\n5. A new chapter awaits at the page devoted to this state’s primary legislative body — uncover the duration of terms served by its members.\n\n6. Consider the distance from the offices that govern to the meeting place of the assembly — how many minutes would it take to drive from one to the other?\n\n7. Transport yourself to an event that highlights athletic prowess in a European country; what height is recorded at the venue for the upcoming games?\n\n8. Of the number you revealed in clue 7, how many characters does it take to express that height in the ancient Roman manner? Count and document your answer.\n\n9. Picture the temperature of 234°C; if you were to convert that into a Fahrenheit-scale offset, what numerical value would result?\n\n10. From the figure derived in clue 9, how many individual digits comprise its sum? Reflect and calculate.\n\n11. As you prepare for future events, convert a distance of five meters into yards — what is the value of that measure?\n\n12. For your final computation, gather the insights from clue 1, clue 2, clue 4, and clue 6, and compute: (your answer from clue 1 + your answer from clue 2 + your answer from clue 4 + your answer from clue 6) modulo 10. Remember, the answer must be a single digit ranging from 0 to 9.",
